Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and slice @zucchini{1}(trimmed and sliced crosswise on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces).
Peel @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced into rounds).

Toss zucchini and @long green pepper{1}(halved, cored, and sliced into ½-inch-thick strips) on
a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @guacamole{½%cup}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon},
and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium-high heat.
Add onion rounds and cook, undisturbed, until deeply browned and tender,
~{2-3%minutes} per side. Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Halve @demi-baguette{2} lengthwise.

> TIP: Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to toast in batches, using a
> large drizzle of olive oil for each batch.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in pan used for onion over medium heat.
Add baguettes, cut sides down, and toast until golden brown, ~{1-3%minutes}.

Spread cut sides of baguettes with half the spicy guacamole. Fill with as many
onion rounds and roasted veggies as you like.

Divide sandwiches, @blue corn tortilla chips{3%ounce}, any remaining onion rounds,
and any remaining roasted veggies between plates. Serve with remaining spicy
guacamole on the side for dipping.